editorialSummary.text: Standard deli offering quick bites, from pancakes & omelets to sandwiches & create-your-own salads.

originalText.text: been here twice now. had the Tuscan flat bread one day and the avacado roll with some seaweed salad the other. AMAZING food! the cashier isn't friendly at all. . . or I would have given 5 stars.

originalText.text: I've been ordering breakfast here for the past couple of weeks. Food is always fresh and tastes great, the cooks are friendly and quick. Place is busy in the mornings, but customers get their orders fast. Unfortunately, they do not have chocolate croissants, but the orange cranberry muffin is absolutely amazing! I thought for being on 58th Street in the city, it would be expensive, but I pay the same amount for the same breakfast in Queens.

originalText.text: Deli is okay. It’s unfortunately the only option or I would likely go elsewhere. Cashier is rude and the prices are ridiculous. I just got charge $7 for grilled cheese. To be clear, that’s two slices of white bread and American cheese. When I questioned why the sandwich was more than an omelette with vegetables the cashier shouted at me “Eggs are eggs! Grilled cheese is grilled cheese!” I’ll be supporting the local carts from now on instead.

originalText.text: Do not come here. Go to oxford cafe (on 59th and between lex and park instead). Here the cashiers are always rude. Once I ordered iced coffee which tasted like watered down coffee with coffee grinds in the bottom. I asked for an exchange and the lady begrudgingly made another. Today I bought a $3 cheesecake but the credit card minimum is $5 so the korean guy at the counter charged me $5 before asking if it was acceptable. I opened my purchase and found a paperclip inside my food.
